<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-651-682  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 651 682.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  June 25 1990 v218 n26A pS10(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Developing a master plan. (development of the Sonet fiber optictelecommunications network interface) (Sonet Special supplement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Warr, Michael; Wilson, Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Sonet, a new fiber optic network interface technology that isbeing introduced into telecommunications networks, is not aservice, but rather functions as a transport interface that letsthe public network provide various different services.andP;  The Sonetinterface development work has been underway since 1984, butstandards for the protocol are not yet established even thoughtelephone companies are anxious to start more widespreadimplementation of Sonet equipment.andP;  The telecommunicationindustry's move toward using this interface started with Sonettransport equipment being used to replace asynchronous equipmentin fiber deployment from point to point.andP;  The next step isunclear, although establishment of Sonet-based fiber rings islikely as soon as the Sonet standards are decided upon.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     SONET (Computer Network Protocol)Telecommunications ServicesTelephone companiesFiber opticsStandards.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>